      "<b>Part 2: Inserting Clip Art and Word Art</b>:<br><br>1. Inserting Clip Art:<br>Open the document where you want to add clip art.<br>Click on the “Insert” tab in the toolbar.<br>Select “Clip Art” or “Pictures” and browse through the available options.<br>Choose the image you like and click 'Insert.'<br><br>2. Inserting Word Art:<br>Click on the “Insert” tab again.<br>Select “Word Art” and choose a style you like.<br>Type the text you want to convert into word art, and it will appear with special effects.<br><br>Demonstration:<br>Show how to insert both clip art and word art.<br>Ensure students understand how to resize and position them after insertion.",
      "<b>Part 3: Moving Clip Art and Word Art</b>:<br><br>After inserting clip art or word art, you can click on it to select it.<br>Once selected, drag the image or text to the desired location in the document.<br>Use the handles (small boxes around the image or text) to adjust its position.<br><br>Demonstration:<br>Show how to click and drag clip art and word art to move them around the page.<br>Explain that students should be careful to avoid overlapping important text or images.",
