      "<b>Part 1: Introduction to Clip Art and Word Art</b>:<br><br>Clip Art: Clip art refers to simple images or illustrations used in digital documents, presentations, and web content. These images are often pre-designed and can be inserted into documents to make them visually appealing.<br><br>Word Art: Word art is a text-based design that allows users to create stylized text with effects such as shadows, outlines, and different fonts. It is commonly used in documents, posters, and presentations to highlight important text or make it more eye-catching.",
      "<b>Part 2: Identifying Icons for Clip Art and Word Art</b>:<br><br>Clip Art Icons: These icons are usually represented as small pictures or images in the toolbar of software programs like Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, or Google Docs. They represent categories such as animals, nature, people, technology, and more. For example, an image of a tree might represent the 'Nature' clip art category.<br><br>Word Art Icons: Word art icons usually display a letter or a word that has different styles applied to it. These can be found in the 'Insert' or 'Text' menu of various programs. The icons often look like stylized text with special effects such as shadows or colors.",
      "<b>Part 3: How Clip Art and Word Art Enhance Documents</b>:<br><br>Clip Art Enhancements: Clip art makes documents more visually appealing and helps explain ideas more clearly. For example, in a presentation about animals, using clip art of different animals can make the presentation more interesting and engaging.<br><br>Word Art Enhancements: Word art makes text stand out. It can be used for titles, headings, or important points in a presentation or document. By changing the font, size, and adding effects, word art draws attention to key information.",
      "<b>Part 4: Understanding the Tools and Menus for Accessing Icons</b>:<br><br>Finding Clip Art Icons: In programs like Microsoft Word or Google Docs, clip art icons can be accessed by selecting the 'Insert' menu and then choosing 'Clip Art' or 'Images.' Students can search for specific images based on categories or keywords (e.g., 'dog' or 'tree').<br><br>Finding Word Art Icons: In programs like Microsoft Word or Google Docs, word art icons are found by selecting 'Insert' and then choosing 'Word Art.' A variety of styles will appear, and students can select the one that best fits their document.",
      "<b>Part 5: Exercise – Identifying and Using Icons</b>:<br><br>1. Task 1: Identifying Clip Art Icons<br>Provide students with a sample document that includes various clip art images.<br>Ask students to identify the clip art icon categories. For example, 'This clip art represents an animal,' 'This clip art represents nature,' and so on.<br><br>2. Task 2: Creating Word Art<br>Have students open a word processing program (e.g., Microsoft Word or Google Docs).<br>Instruct students to create a word art design using their name or a favorite word. Encourage them to explore different styles, fonts, and effects like shadows or outlines."
